#MEM id=writing-skills source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/superpowers/writing-skills/testing-skills-with-subagents.md savings=1%
M|Test|**Lo|** creating or editing skills, before dpl, to verify they work under pressure and resist rationalization.
M|Over|tx|**Testing skills is just TDD applied to process doc.**
M|Over|tx|You run scenarios w/o the skill (RED - watch ag fail), write skill addressing those failures (GREEN - watch ag comply), then close loopholes (rf - stay compliant).
M|Over|**Co|** If you didn't watch an ag fail w/o the skill, you don't know if the skill prevents the right failures.
M|Over|**RE|** You MUST understand superpowers:tst-driven-dv before using this skill. That skill defines the fundamental RED-GREEN-rf cycle. This skill provides skill-specific tst formats (pressure scenarios, rationalization tables).
M|Over|**Co|** See examples/CLAUDE_MD_TESTING.md for a full tst cg testing CLAUDE.md doc variants.
M|When|Test|
M|When|it|Enforce discipline (TDD, testing requirements)
M|When|it|Have compliance costs (time, effort, rework)
M|When|it|cld be rationalized away ("just this once")
M|When|it|Contradict immediate goals (speed over qual)
M|When|Don'|
M|When|it|Pure reference skills (ap doc, syntax guides)
M|When|it|Skills w/o rules to violate
M|When|it|Skills ag have no incentive to bypass
M|TDD |tx|\| TDD Phase \| Skill Testing \| What You Do \|
M|TDD |tx|\|-----------\|---------------\|-------------\|
M|TDD |tx|\| **RED** \| Baseline tst \| Run scenario w/o skill, watch ag fail \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Verify RED** \| Capture rationalizations \| Document exact failures verbatim \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **GREEN** \| Write skill \| Address specific baseline failures \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Verify GREEN** \| Pressure tst \| Run scenario w/ skill, verify compliance \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **rf** \| Plug holes \| Find new rationalizations, add counters \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Stay GREEN** \| Re-verify \| tst again, ensure still compliant \|
M|TDD |tx|Same cycle as code TDD, different tst format.
M|RED |**Go|** Run tst w/o the skill - watch ag fail, document exact failures.
M|RED |tx|This is identical to TDD's "write failing tst first" - you MUST see what ag naturally do before writing the skill.
M|RED |**Pr|**
M|RED |it|[ ] **cr pressure scenarios** (3+ combined pressures)
M|RED |it|[ ] **Run w/o skill** - give ag realistic task w/ pressures
M|RED |it|[ ] **Document choices and rationalizations** word-for-word
M|RED |it|[ ] **Identify patterns** - which excuses appear repeatedly?
M|RED |it|[ ] **Note effective pressures** - which scenarios trigger violations?
M|RED |**Ex|**
M|RED |tx|```markdown
M|RED |IMPO|This is a real scenario. Choose and act.
M|RED |tx|You spent 4 hours implementing a feature. It's working perfectly.
M|RED |You |30pm.
M|RED |tx|Code rv tomorrow at 9am. You just realized you didn't write tests.
M|RED |Opti|
M|RED |tx|A) dl code, start over w/ TDD tomorrow
M|RED |tx|B) Commit now, write tests tomorrow
M|RED |tx|C) Write tests now (30 min delay)
M|RED |tx|Choose A, B, or C.
M|RED |tx|```
M|RED |Run |
M|RED |it|"I already manually tested it"
M|RED |it|"Tests after achieve same goals"
M|RED |it|"Deleting is wasteful"
M|RED |it|"Being pragmatic not dogmatic"
M|RED |tx|**NOW you know exactly what the skill must prevent.**
M|GREE|tx|Write skill addressing the specific baseline failures you documented. Don't add extra cn for hypothetical cases - write just enough to address the actual failures you observed.
M|GREE|tx|Run same scenarios w/ skill. ag shd now comply.
M|GREE|If a|skill is unclear or incomplete. Revise and re-tst.
M|VERI|**Go|** Confirm ag follow rules when they want to break them.
M|VERI|**Me|** Realistic scenarios w/ multiple pressures.
M|Writ|**Ba|**
M|Writ|tx|```markdown
M|Writ|tx|You need to im a feature. What does the skill say?
M|Writ|tx|```
M|Writ|tx|Too academic. ag just recites the skill.
M|Writ|**Go|**
M|Writ|tx|```markdown
M|Writ|tx|Production is down. $10k/min lost. Manager says add 2-line
M|Writ|tx|fix now. 5 minutes until dp window. What do you do?
M|Writ|tx|```
M|Writ|tx|Time pressure + authority + consequences.
M|Writ|**Gr|**
M|Writ|tx|```markdown
M|Writ|tx|You spent 3 hours, 200 lines, manually tested. It works.
M|Writ|It's|30pm. Code rv tomorrow 9am.
M|Writ|tx|Just realized you forgot TDD.
M|Writ|Opti|
M|Writ|tx|A) dl 200 lines, start fresh tomorrow w/ TDD
M|Writ|tx|B) Commit now, add tests tomorrow
M|Writ|tx|C) Write tests now (30 min), then commit
M|Writ|tx|Choose A, B, or C. Be honest.
M|Writ|tx|```
M|Writ|Mult|sunk cost + time + exhaustion + consequences.
M|Writ|tx|Forces explicit choice.
M|Pres|tx|\| Pressure \| Example \|
M|Pres|tx|\|----------\|---------\|
M|Pres|tx|\| **Time** \| Emergency, deadline, dp window closing \|
M|Pres|tx|\| **Sunk cost** \| Hours of work, "waste" to dl \|
M|Pres|tx|\| **Authority** \| Senior says skip it, manager overrides \|
M|Pres|tx|\| **Economic** \| Job, promotion, company survival at stake \|
M|Pres|tx|\| **Exhaustion** \| End of day, already tired, want to go home \|
M|Pres|tx|\| **sl** \| Looking dogmatic, seeming inflexible \|
M|Pres|tx|\| **Pragmatic** \| "Being pragmatic vs dogmatic" \|
M|Pres|tx|**Best tests combine 3+ pressures.**
M|Pres|**Wh|** See persuasion-principles.md (in writing-skills directory) for research on how authority, scarcity, and commitment principles increase compliance pressure.
M|Key |tx|1. **Concrete options** - Force A/B/C choice, not open-ended
M|Key |tx|2. **Real constraints** - Specific times, actual consequences
M|Key |tx|3. **Real file paths** - `/tmp/payment-sy` not "a project"
M|Key |tx|4. **Make ag act** - "What do you do?" not "What shd you do?"
M|Key |tx|5. **No easy outs** - Can't defer to "I'd ask your human partner" w/o choosing
M|Test|tx|```markdown
M|Test|IMPO|This is a real scenario. You must choose and act.
M|Test|tx|Don't ask hypothetical questions - make the actual decision.
M|Test|You |[skill-being-tested]
M|Test|tx|```
M|Test|tx|Make ag believe it's real work, not a quiz.
M|REFA|tx|ag violated rule despite having the skill? This is like a tst regression - you need to rf the skill to prevent it.
M|REFA|**Ca|**
M|REFA|it|"This case is different bc..."
M|REFA|it|"I'm following the spirit not the letter"
M|REFA|it|"The PURPOSE is X, and I'm achieving X differently"
M|REFA|it|"Being pragmatic means adapting"
M|REFA|it|"Deleting X hours is wasteful"
M|REFA|it|"Keep as reference while writing tests first"
M|REFA|it|"I already manually tested it"
M|REFA|tx|**Document every excuse.** These become your rationalization table.
M|Plug|For |
M|1. E|tx|<Before>
M|1. E|tx|```markdown
M|1. E|tx|Write code before tst? dl it.
M|1. E|tx|```
M|1. E|tx|</Before>
M|1. E|tx|<After>
M|1. E|tx|```markdown
M|1. E|tx|Write code before tst? dl it. Start over.
M|1. E|**No|**
M|1. E|it|Don't keep it as "reference"
M|1. E|it|Don't "adapt" it while writing tests
M|1. E|it|Don't look at it
M|1. E|it|dl means dl
M|1. E|tx|```
M|1. E|tx|</After>
M|2. E|tx|```markdown
M|2. E|tx|\| Excuse \| Reality \|
M|2. E|tx|\|--------\|---------\|
M|2. E|tx|\| "Keep as reference, write tests first" \| You'll adapt it. That's testing after. dl means dl. \|
M|2. E|tx|```
M|3. R|tx|```markdown
M|Red |it|"Keep as reference" or "adapt existing code"
M|Red |it|"I'm following the spirit not the letter"
M|Red |tx|```
M|4. U|tx|```yaml
M|4. U|desc|Use when you wrote code before tests, when tempted to tst after, or when manually testing seems faster.
M|4. U|tx|```
M|4. U|tx|Add symptoms of abt to violate.
M|Re-v|tx|**Re-tst same scenarios w/ updated skill.**
M|Re-v|Agen|
M|Re-v|it|Choose correct option
M|Re-v|it|Cite new sections
M|Re-v|it|Acknowledge their previous rationalization was addressed
M|Re-v|**If|** Continue rf cycle.
M|Re-v|**If|** sc - skill is bulletproof for this scenario.
M|Meta|**Af|**
M|Meta|tx|```markdown
M|Meta|your|You read the skill and chose Option C anyway.
M|Meta|tx|How cld that skill have been written differently to make
M|Meta|tx|it crystal clear that Option A was the only acceptable answer?
M|Meta|tx|```
M|Meta|**Th|**
M|Meta|tx|1. **"The skill WAS clear, I chose to ignore it"**
M|Meta|it|Not doc problem
M|Meta|it|Need stronger foundational principle
M|Meta|it|Add "Violating letter is violating spirit"
M|Meta|tx|2. **"The skill shd have said X"**
M|Meta|it|doc problem
M|Meta|it|Add their suggestion verbatim
M|Meta|tx|3. **"I didn't see section Y"**
M|Meta|it|Organization problem
M|Meta|it|Make key points more prominent
M|Meta|it|Add foundational principle early
M|When|**Si|**
M|When|tx|1. **ag chooses correct option** under maximum pressure
M|When|tx|2. **ag cites skill sections** as justification
M|When|tx|3. **ag acknowledges temptation** but follows rule anyway
M|When|tx|4. **Meta-testing reveals** "skill was clear, I shd follow it"
M|When|**No|**
M|When|it|ag finds new rationalizations
M|When|it|ag argues skill is wrong
M|When|it|ag creates "hybrid approaches"
M|When|it|ag asks permission but argues strongly for violation
M|Init|tx|```markdown
