M|Test|Befo|
M|Test|**RE|**
M|Test|it|[ ] Created pressure scenarios (3+ combined pressures)
M|Test|it|[ ] Ran scenarios w/o skill (baseline)
M|Test|it|[ ] Documented ag failures and rationalizations verbatim
M|Test|**GR|**
M|Test|it|[ ] Wrote skill addressing specific baseline failures
M|Test|it|[ ] Ran scenarios w/ skill
M|Test|it|[ ] ag now complies
M|Test|**RE|**
M|Test|it|[ ] Identified NEW rationalizations from testing
M|Test|it|[ ] Added explicit counters for each loophole
M|Test|it|[ ] Updated rationalization table
M|Test|it|[ ] Updated red flags list
M|Test|it|[ ] Updated description w/ violation symptoms
M|Test|it|[ ] Re-tested - ag still complies
M|Test|it|[ ] Meta-tested to verify clarity
M|Test|it|[ ] ag follows rule under maximum pressure
M|Comm|tx|**❌ Writing skill before testing (skipping RED)**
M|Comm|tx|Reveals what YOU think needs preventing, not what ACTUALLY needs preventing.
M|Comm|fix|Always run baseline scenarios first.
M|Comm|tx|**❌ Not watching tst fail properly**
M|Comm|tx|Running only academic tests, not real pressure scenarios.
M|Comm|fix|Use pressure scenarios that make ag WANT to violate.
M|Comm|tx|**❌ Weak tst cases (single pressure)**
M|Comm|tx|ag resist single pressure, break under multiple.
M|Comm|fix|Combine 3+ pressures (time + sunk cost + exhaustion).
M|Comm|tx|**❌ Not capturing exact failures**
M|Comm|tx|"ag was wrong" doesn't tell you what to prevent.
M|Comm|fix|Document exact rationalizations verbatim.
M|Comm|tx|**❌ Vague fixes (adding generic counters)**
M|Comm|tx|"Don't cheat" doesn't work. "Don't keep as reference" does.
M|Comm|fix|Add explicit negations for each specific rationalization.
M|Comm|tx|**❌ Stopping after first pass**
M|Comm|tx|Tests pass once ≠ bulletproof.
M|Comm|fix|Continue rf cycle until no new rationalizations.
M|Quic|tx|\| TDD Phase \| Skill Testing \| sc Criteria \|
M|Quic|tx|\|-----------\|---------------\|------------------\|
M|Quic|tx|\| **RED** \| Run scenario w/o skill \| ag fails, document rationalizations \|
M|Quic|tx|\| **Verify RED** \| Capture exact wording \| Verbatim doc of failures \|
M|Quic|tx|\| **GREEN** \| Write skill addressing failures \| ag now complies w/ skill \|
M|Quic|tx|\| **Verify GREEN** \| Re-tst scenarios \| ag follows rule under pressure \|
M|Quic|tx|\| **rf** \| Close loopholes \| Add counters for new rationalizations \|
M|Quic|tx|\| **Stay GREEN** \| Re-verify \| ag still complies after refactoring \|
M|The |tx|**Skill creation IS TDD. Same principles, same cycle, same benefits.**
M|The |tx|If you wouldn't write code w/o tests, don't write skills w/o testing them on ag.
M|The |tx|RED-GREEN-rf for doc works exactly like RED-GREEN-rf for code.
M|Real|From|
M|Real|it|6 RED-GREEN-rf iterations to bulletproof
M|Real|it|Baseline testing revealed 10+ unique rationalizations
M|Real|it|Each rf closed specific loopholes
M|Real|- Fi|100% compliance under maximum pressure
M|Real|it|Same process works for any discipline-enforcing skill